Personal configuration for awesome WM

Diffrent with default configs:

1. mod + c = mod + shift + c
2. mod + i = show client informations, useful when write rules
3. mod + enter = run or raise terminal
4. mod + shift + enter = run terminal
5. mod + BackSpace = raise opened VIM
6. mod + ` = run or raise browser

Themes:

1. basiclly default awesome wm theme
2. xcompmgr with fading and shading
3. one level menu, no groups, with icons
   Tips: mod + w = open menu
4. archlinux icon at as root menu
5. Wallpaper use nitrogen --restore, so you can change your wallpaper without edit codes.

Planning:

term,EDITOR,Browser,Mail,Chat,Music, all in "run or raise" mode
(vim ?), cmus goes to own tag when title change
others goes to "others" tag,
seprate very personal configs, for easy share and maintain
Hide terminal,EDITORs,Browser in taskbar, taskbar is for others

